enum.name: FetchLaterBrowserMetricType

int.label: kAbortedByInitiator: FetchLater request is aborted by its initiator

enum.int:
Recorded once every time a scheduled FetchLater request is aborted in the browser process. It happens when JavaScript code explicitly aborts a FetchLater request, and gets propagated to the browser process.
This number should be compared with `kAbortedByUser` in `FetchLater.Renderer.Metrics`.

int.label: kStartedAfterInitiatorDisconnected: FetchLater request is started after its initiator is disconnected

enum.int:
Recorded once every time a scheduled FetchLater request is started after its initiator renderer is disconnected from browser.
This number should be compared with `kContextDestroyed` in `FetchLater.Renderer.Metrics`.

int.label: kStartedByInitiator: FetchLater request is explicitly started by its initiator

enum.int:
Recorded once every time a scheduled FetchLater request is explicitly asked to started by its initiator renderer in the browser.
This number should be compared with `kActivatedByTimeout` in `FetchLater.Renderer.Metrics`, and it should <= `FetchLater.Browser.Total.Started`.

int.label: kCancelledAfterTimeLimit: FetchLater request is cancelled after internal time limit

enum.int: Recorded once every time a scheduled or a started FetchLater request is cancelled by the browser after some internal time limit.

int.label: kStartedWhenShutdown: FetchLater request is started when browser is shutting down earlier than renderer

enum.int: Recorded once every time a scheduled or FetchLater request is started when browser is shutting down. This does not include cases when renderer terminates earlier, which is logged as kStartedAfterInitiatorDisconnected.

enum.name: FetchLaterRendererMetricType

int.label: kAbortedByUser: FetchLater request is aborted by user

enum.int:
Recorded once every time a scheduled FetchLater request is aborted in a renderer process. It happens when JavaScript code explicitly aborts a FetchLater request.
This number should be compared with `FetchLater.Browser.Metrics.AbortedByInitiator`.

int.label: kContextDestroyed: FetchLater's context is destroyed (implying activated by browser)

enum.int:
Recorded once every time a scheduled FetchLater request is activated on Fetch context being destroyed.
This number should be compared with `FetchLater.Browser.Metrics.kStartedByInitiator`.

int.label: kActivatedByTimeout: FetchLater request is activated by user specified timeout

enum.int:
Recorded once every time a scheduled FetchLater request is terminated (and then gets sent) due to context (renderer) destroyed. It is not equivalent to the total number of internal "TERMINATED" states of a FetchLater request, which can be terminated for other reasons like aborted by users.
This number should be compared with `FetchLater.Browser.Metrics.StartedAfterInitiatorDisconnected`.

int.label: kActivatedOnEnteredBackForwardCache: FetchLater request is activated when the context is put into BackForwardCache

enum.int: Recorded once every time a scheduled FetchLater request is activated on entering BackForwardCache in a renderer process. It happens only when BackgroundSync permission of the FetchContext is off.

int.label: SUBDOMAIN_INVERSE_MATCH2: The DNS is a subdomain of the URL

int.label: SUBDOMAIN_OUTSIDE_WILDCARD2: The URL is outside the scope of the wildcard certificate

enum.int: This cause is recorded only if the SSL error is CERT_COMMON_NAME_INVALID, we have received a wildcard certificate and the scope of a wildcard certificate is too narrow for the hostname. This case is not recorded if the host name is not a known TLD.

int.label: LIKELY_MULTI_TENANT_HOSTING2: The certificate is a shared certificate

enum.int: This cause is recorded only for CERT_COMMON_NAME_INVALID errors where the certificate contains numerous unrelated DNS names. This case is not recorded if the host name is not a known TLD.

int.label: LIKELY_SAME_DOMAIN2: Cert likely belongs to the same domain

enum.int: This case is recorded if the SSL error is CERT_COMMON_NAME_INVALID error and the hostname in request URL has the same domain (effective TLD + 1 label) as a SubjectAltName in the certificate. This case is not recorded if the host name is not a known TLD.
